    <data key="d0">Swimming Australia Relay Team Selection App</data>
    <data key="d1">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1VcpCVe3tLQ</data>
    <data key="d2">This architecture supports the Australian national swim team ('The Dolphins') in selecting optimal relay teams. It involves a data pipeline for ingesting and transforming race results and athlete information, a machine learning workflow for predicting swim times and optimal relay lineups, and a web application for coaches to interact with the predictions. Key requirements include handling various data formats, providing a SQL interface for data scientists, and automating model retraining and deployment. The system refreshes data every 15 minutes during competition and weekly otherwise. It also provides tools for coaches to experiment with scenarios and validate model outputs.</data>
    <data key="d3">data_ingestion, interactive, compute_intensive, control</data>
    <data key="d4">True</data>
  </graph>
</graphml>
